ALGORITHM

1.	Start
2.	Initialize DPTR = 4600
3.	Read the number of data (N) to be transferred from memory location 4600H and store it in the R1 register 
4.	Increment DPTR
5.	Read the next number and store it in the R2 register
6.	Increment DPH (46xx to 47xx)
7.	Read the next number and store it in the accumulator
8.	Exchange the content of the accumulator and R2 register
9.	Store the content of the accumulator in memory location (47xx)
10.	Decrement DPH (47xx to 46xx)
11.	Store the content of R2 in memory location (46xx)
12.	Decrement the R1 register and if it is not equal to zero go to step 4 else go to step 13
13.	Stop

